Multiple binary response

Source: R/ses.moecalc.R
seMRprops.Rd

SE's for multiple binary response

Usage

seMRprops(obj)

Arguments

obj

something that can be turned into a matrix

Value

an ses.moecalc object

Author

Junjie Zeng

Examples

x <- data.frame(
    v1 = rbinom(20, 1, 0.8),
    v2 = rbinom(20, 1, 0.3),
    v3 = rbinom(20, 1, 0.5)
)
seMRprops(x)
#> $ses
#>         v1         v2         v3 
#> 0.07984360 0.09682458 0.11180340 
#> 
#> $ses.diffs
#>           v1        v2        v3
#> v1 0.0000000 0.1095445 0.1066536
#> v2 0.1095445 0.0000000 0.1391941
#> v3 0.1066536 0.1391941 0.0000000
#> 
#> attr(,"class")
#> [1] "ses.moecalc"
